			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Semi-coke is the solid residue obtained by carbonization especially of coal at a relatively low temperature that is in general softer and more friable than coke from carbonization at higher temperatures. It gives a hot smokeless fire and can be used as a domestic fuel. It is also used as a carbonaceous reductant for industrial silicon to improve the exergy efficiency and reduce the specific energy consumption. The use of semi-coke instead of anthracite coal for blast furnace injection to reduce ironmaking costs is becoming increasingly popular.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">半焦是煤炭在相对较低的温度下碳化得到的固体残渣，一般比在较高温度下碳化得到的焦炭更软、更易碎。它能产生无烟的热火，可用作家用燃料。它还可用作工业硅的碳质还原剂，以提高放能效率，降低比能耗。使用半焦代替无烟煤进行高炉喷吹以降低炼铁成本的做法正变得越来越流行。</common:generalComment>
